    {
      "id": "note-1771052154530-3",
      "title": "This Workflow",
      "content": "The notes in this workflow include a field named \"Files\" which indicate which files might be relevant to each task.\n\nAll filepaths are relative to the main project directory.\n\nCAPITALS indicate a placeholder. For example, If we are working on a task called \"Update sidebar,\" and the \"Files\" field includes \"EATURE-NAME-design-spec.txt\" You might look for files called \"update-sidebar-design-spec.txt\" or \"new-sidebar-tool-design-spec.txt\"\n\nRead the file if it exists, ask to create the file if it doesn't exist.\n\nYou only need to read each file once, not every time its referenced. \n\nIn some cases, the text body of the note doesn't include specific instructions. Refer to your context about the listed files to determine your next steps.|\n\n#claude",
      "hashtags": [
        "#claude"
      ],
      "fields": {},
      "position": {
        "x": 40.411984062472925,
        "y": -532.0054200537134
      },
